This paper deals with multiobjective optimization and anomaly detection, which are topics that are commonly studied in the machine learning and data science communities. The use of partial differential equations (PDEs) to solve these problems is a novel approach that is likely to be of interest to researchers in the areas of machine learning (cs.LG), numerical analysis (cs.NA), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
